data.description: Active Under Contract - Accepting Back Up Offers. Embrace the possibilities of the new year and this Spring Hill pool home! It has massive potential for savvy investors or first-time homebuyers, and would be an excellent candidate for all types of renovation loans. Located in a neighborhood with no HOA fees or restrictions, it has a double-gated carport that opens up to the backyard, so it can easily accommodate parking for a boat or an RV. Through the screened front porch, you'll find an open floor plan that was designed for modern living; the spacious living and dining rooms offer space for family gatherings or entertaining, and tile flooring allows ease of maintenance. The galley-style kitchen has lots of cabinet and counter space, plus a pantry for your storage needs. If you are in need of flexible space, there's a uniquely-positioned bonus room that would make an excellent nursery, home office, or even a 4th bedroom. It is accessible via the primary bedroom or separately via the laundry room, so theoretically, it could even be an in-law suite. The primary bedroom does have an ensuite bathroom with a walk-in shower and a large closet. The remaining guest bedrooms are quite sizable; they share a bathroom with a tub/shower combo. Step through sliding glass doors in the dining room when it's time for fun in the Florida sun! The sport pool - shallow on each end, deep in the middle - has a newer pool pump. It overlooks the backyard, which is surrounded by vinyl fencing for that added level of safety and privacy. In addition to at least one fruit-producing lemon tree, there are two sheds out back, as well as a former pond and seating area, and some raised beds. The wiring and plumbing still exists on one of the sheds (it even had an outdoor shower); it could be transformed back into a functional workshop so you have the space to take your side hustle to the next level. With a little love and attention, this backyard could become an absolute haven for you and your family! All of this is situated close to schools, parks, shopping, and dining options. Discover the beauty of the Adventure Coast at Weeki Wachee Springs State Park less than 3 miles to the west; you can launch your kayak or canoe and paddle the crystal clear waters of the river, enjoy the water park during the summer months, and even see real mermaid magic! You're centrally located between US-19 and the Suncoast Parkway for easy access to Homosassa, the sponge docks of Tarpon, the beaches of Clearwater, and all the attractions and amenities of Tampa. Orlando and its popular theme parks are less than 2 hours to the east, too. Seize the opportunity to start fresh - create a space that resonates with your unique story! Call us and schedule your private tour today.
